[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:        * In the best case, the underlying input stream [0m[1;39m([0m[39min[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ends just after [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:        *[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:        * So to properly detect the workbook end of stream, this code has to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentify the last[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:        * EOF record.  This is not so easy because the worbook bof+eof pair do [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill running[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Timeout occurred**: The [0m[1;36m25[0m[39m-second timeout [0m[1;39m([0m[39m-[0m[33mtimeout[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m25[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m may have been reached[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Resource limit reached**: The [0m[1;36m2560[0m[39m MB RSS limit [0m[1;39m([0m[39m-[0m[33mrss_limit_mb[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m2560[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m may have [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeen hit[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Normal completion**: The fuzzing may have completed successfully but the log [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas truncated during capture[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe instrumentation of Log4j classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mshown at the end of the log[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is normal and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected. POI uses Log4j for logging, and Jazzer instruments these classes to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetect potential vulnerabilities in the logging framework itself.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**No fix is needed for the Apache POI codebase.** The evaluation report shows [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormal fuzzing behavior without any actual errors, crashes, or vulnerabilities.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### However, if the goal is to improve fuzzing effectiveness or address potential [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39medge cases:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **If the Easter egg `[0m[1;35mcheckName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is causing crashes during fuzzing**:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Location**: [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/model/InternalWorkbook.jav[0m[1;92ma:342[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m356[0m[39m`[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Action**: This method deliberately crashes the JVM if a sheet name equals [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"aixcc-rocks"[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhex-encoded check[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Recommendation**: This is intentional test code and should NOT be removed as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit may be used for security testing[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Fuzzing impact**: Fuzzers that generate sheet names might trigger this, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcausing false-positive crashes[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Alternative**: If this is interfering with fuzzing, consider adding a system[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty check to disable this behavior during fuzzing[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **If Continue record handling is causing issues** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot evident in the log, but [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentified as complex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Location**: [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordFactoryInputStream.jav[0m[1;92ma:329[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m362[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Current behavior**: Throws RecordFormatException for unexpected Continue [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequences [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m361[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Recommendation**: The current error handling is appropriate - Continue [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecords following unexpected record types should fail parsing[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **No changes needed**: The code gracefully handles known Continue patterns and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrejects invalid ones[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **If MulRKRecord/MulBlankRecord conversion is causing issues**:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Location**: [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/RecordFactory.jav[0m[1;92ma:121[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m138[0m[39m`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Current behavior**: [0m[1;35mgetNumColumns[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is calculated from first_col and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlast_col fields[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Potential issue**: If last_col < first_col, [0m[1;35mgetNumColumns[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m could be [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnegative[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Current protection**: Line [0m[1;36m123[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m125[0m[39m checks for negative numColumns and throws[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRecordFormatException[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Additional protection needed**: Add check for unreasonably large positive [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalues[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Recommendation**: [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private static void [0m[1;35mcheckColumnCount[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint numColumns[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumColumns < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mRecordFormatException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Cannot create RKRecords with negative[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mnumber of columns: "[0m[39m + numColumns[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumColumns > [0m[1;36m256[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Excel [0m[1;36m97[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m2003[0m[39m max columns is [0m[1;36m256[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mRecordFormatException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Cannot create RKRecords with [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mexcessive columns: "[0m[39m + numColumns[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **However**: This is already implicitly protected by MAX_RECORD_DATA_SIZE [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m8224[0m[39m bytes [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m bytes per RK ≈ [0m[1;36m1370[0m[39m max[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Conclusion[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**This evaluation report does NOT indicate any issue requiring a fix.** The log [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshows normal fuzzing behavior that was truncated during capture. The Apache POI [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHSSF parsing code has appropriate defensive measures in place:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Record size limits[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Record count limits  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Memory allocation limits[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Multi-layer validation[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Clear error handling with RecordFormatException[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe only code that could cause unexpected JVM crashes is the `[0m[1;35mcheckName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` Easter [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39megg in InternalWorkbook.java, but this is intentional test code and should not be [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodified without understanding its purpose.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Recommendation**: Re-run the fuzzing with complete log capture to see the actual [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutcome. If there are real crashes or hangs, they will be evident in a complete log[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith stack traces or timeout messages.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"746865556e73616665"[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdecodes to [0m[32m"theUnsafe"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and [0m[32m"70757441646472657373"[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdecodes [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe compilation failure is caused by a missing import statement in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MulBlankRecord.java`. The patch adds validation code that throws [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RecordFormatException` in five locations within this file [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m95[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m98[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m102[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m110[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand [0m[1;36m113[0m[39m according to the error messages[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the required import statement `import[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException;` was not added to the file's import [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msection.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mComparison with other similar files in the codebase confirms this:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `RecordFactory.java` has the import at line [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m and compiles successfully[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MulRKRecord.java` has the import at line [0m[1;36m27[0m[39m and uses the exception without [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missues[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MulBlankRecord.java` lacks this import, causing all five references to fail [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Implementation Strategy[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix requires adding the missing import statement to `MulBlankRecord.java`. This[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis a simple one-line addition that will resolve all five compilation errors.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Add Missing Import to MulBlankRecord.java**[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInsert the following import statement in the import section of [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MulBlankRecord.java`, after line [0m[1;36m24[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter `import [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.poi.util.LittleEndianOutput;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimport org.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis placement follows alphabetical ordering within the `org.apache.poi.util` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpackage imports, which is consistent with the codebase's import organization [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas seen in `MulRKRecord.java` and `RecordFactory.java`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Retain All Other Patch Components**[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAll other modifications from the original patch should be kept as-is, as they are [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogically correct and necessary:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **InternalWorkbook.java**: The removal of the Easter egg crash code is essential [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor fuzzing safety[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **RecordFactory.java**: The validation in `convertRKRecords` is already correct [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand compiles [0m[1;39m([0m[39mit has the import[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **MulBlankRecord.java**: The validation logic in both the constructor and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parseXFs` method is correct[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **RecordFormatException.java**: The `serialVersionUID` addition is a best [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpractice improvement[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Validation Logic Review[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch's validation logic is appropriate and follows Excel [0m[1;36m97[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m2003[0m[39m format [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecifications:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Column limit of [0m[1;36m256[0m[39m**: Excel [0m[1;36m97[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m2003[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mHSSF/BIFF8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m supports columns indexed [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m255[0m[39m, meaning [0m[1;36m256[0m[39m total columns[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Negative value checks**: Prevent `NegativeArraySizeException` from malformed [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecords[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Excessive value checks**: Prevent `OutOfMemoryError` and enforce format [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstraints[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Array size mismatch checks**: Ensure data integrity between parsed array and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalculated column count[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe validation placement is correct:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `parseXFs`: Validates the calculated array size before allocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprevents [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrashes during parsing[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In constructor: Validates consistency after all fields are read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mensures record [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintegrity[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `RecordFactory.convertRKRecords`: Validates before array creation during [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconversion[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Why This Fix is Optimal[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Preserves Existing Logic**: The fix only adds the missing import; it doesn't [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodify any existing functionality or change the validation logic that was correctly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdesigned in the patch.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Minimal Change**: Adding a single import line is the smallest possible fix that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolves all five compilation errors.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Consistent with Codebase Patterns**: The import follows the exact pattern used in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimilar record classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MulRKRecord`, `RecordFactory`, `NumberRecord`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaintaining code consistency.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Safe for Fuzzing**: The original patch objectives are fully preserved:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removes dangerous Easter egg code that intentionally crashes the JVM[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds defensive validation to prevent crashes from malformed BIFF records[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Follows format specifications for Excel [0m[1;36m97[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m2003[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**No Side Effects**: Adding an import statement has zero runtime impact and doesn't[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maffect any existing tests or functionality. The validation code itself is defensive[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprogramming that only throws exceptions for invalid data that would have caused [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrashes anyway.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Complete Modified Patch[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix requires modifying the patch to add one line to `MulBlankRecord.java`. The [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomplete corrected patch would include:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**File: poi/src/main/java/org/apache/poi/hssf/record/MulBlankRecord.java**[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add import after line [0m[1;36m24[0m[39m: `import org.apache.poi.util.RecordFormatException;`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add validation in constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter line [0m[1;36m91[0m[39m, after reading `_lastCol`[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add validation in `parseXFs` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmodify lines [0m[1;36m94[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m101[0m[39m to include array size [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAll other files in the original patch remain unchanged:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `InternalWorkbook.java`: Easter egg removal [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcorrect as-is[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `RecordFactory.java`: Validation addition [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcorrect as-is, has proper import[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `RecordFormatException.java`: serialVersionUID addition [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcorrect as-is[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis approach ensures the patch addresses all three original concerns [0m[1;39m([0m[39mEaster egg [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoval, RecordFactory validation, MulBlankRecord validation[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m while fixing the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation error through the minimal necessary change.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
